-- Praxair first-quarter earnings climb
-- 
-- Wed Apr 25, 2007 6:58am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/25/us-praxair-results-idUSN2522902220070425

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Industrial gas supplier Praxair Inc. ( PX.N ) said on Wednesday first-quarter earnings rose, spurred by strong volume growth in all its major end markets. 

 Net income rose to $265 million, or 81 cents a share, from $225 million, or 68 cents a share, a year earlier. Analysts on average were expecting earnings of 80 cents per share, according to Reuters Estimates. Sales in the quarter rose 7 percent to $2.18 billion, from $2.03 billion a year ago. The company expects second quarter earnings in the range of 83 cents to 87 cents a share. Wall Street expects the company to earn 85 cents a share. For the full year of 2007, Praxair expects sales growth in the range of 8 percent to 10 percent and earnings between $3.35 and $3.50 a share. The company expects full-year capital expenditures to be in the range of $1.1 billion to $1.2 billion. (Additional reporting by Christopher Kaufman)